rComments: His lectures are dull, but are necessary for the assignments. A good course if you like law as it is more case study based.

Really enjoyed his lectures. His interest and knowledge in the material made me want to come to class. He sometimes talks a bit too fast, and overall you have to work harder than usual to do well. All in all though it is worth it.
Ron is U of T's best professor. He is brilliant and portrays that through his lectures. He cares for every student and his lectures are clear. He expects his students to work hard- be ready to work
The best professor I had in university. Very good at explaining sometimes very challenging material, approachable, funny, and very engaging. His class was the highlight of my last year.

By far the best prof I've ever had. Made class fun to go to, had very clear lecture slides and answered questions to clarify when asked in class. Would go over the cases in class to make sure everyone understood. He's hilarious and his assignments were fair. Wish he was teaching more classes.

Great lecturer. Real funny guy. Very likeable too. Although sometimes he could clarify concepts little bit (should't be a problem if someone asks him to clarify in class)he teaches very well. You won't have any problems with him. Also, his assignments were reasonable for a 200 lvl course-unlike davies and her final exam. God...
I'm third year and he has, so far, been my favourite prof!!!! He's HILARIOUS and brilliant!!!

Okay, so I have only had one class so far, but if that class is any indication of what the year will be like, then this guy is the best prof I've had at U of T to date. He's hilarious and shows real interest in the material. I'll post again at the end of the year to see if he is still the coolest guy ever.

I love Levi! Why can't he teach more undergrad courses? He's so enthusiastic and clear with the cases, great for an intro course when you're not use to case readings. He's the reason I knew Criminology was for me!
he's the best professor EVER. i'm so greatful to be in his class.

Prof Levi is a definite asset to U of T.  He covers all the material with great enthusiasm and makes lectures interesting and enjoyable.  He is very down to earth, approachable and makes difficult material easy to understand.  Take his class if you have the opportunity!

I LOVED PROF.LEVI!! He is by far one of the greatest profs at UofT! He made every class enjoyable. I don't think I've ever walked out of one of his classes without laughing at least 3/4 times. I miss him so much! we have a new prof now..and ...it's just not the same. I really wish he could teach some more undergrad courses.
Clear, intelligent, hilarious, brimming with diet coke.

Levi is great!  The guy has tons of energy and personality which really keeps the class up tempo.  If you have done some of the reading then what he is saying makes lots of sense and definately helps to clarify the sometimes dense readings.  Great prof and class overall.
amazing lectures, very clear and overall very understanding. Best prof ever.
He was great. He didn't try TOO hard - it's hella better than profs who don't try at all. While Prof. Young was fun, I think Prof. Levi did a much better job with this course.
He made sure we understood EVERYTHING.. and his slides were so detailed. Will miss him dearly. But Alan Young is a great replacement.

The best professor i had in my life! class was never boring, his notes were AMAZING! he make sure u understand everything before he goes on to the next topic. I have never learned so much in a course. He's unbelievably amazing, if u don't take his course it's ur loss!
aww, he's so precious. He can really make you laugh, especially with his little slips of the tongue. Taogh material, but he does EVRYTHING he can to make you understand..gonna miss him (tear)
The best prof I had in 2nd year...funny, smart, passionate.  I look forward to more classes taught by him in the future.

Levi's great!  I get a little sleepy in his lectures but not nearly as much as other classes.  He really knows the course material well, I would definitely take it again.  His T.A.s are great...oh and he bought us timbits because he wanted to get us a treat for being in class one day :D.
awesome!

Prof Levi is the most amazing prof that I have had in 2 years.  Very understanding, compassionate, and actually interested in his students. Great guy, who cares.  A lot of work, but I learned the most in this class than all of my others.  Interesting course material, delivered clearly and simple
good prof - really cares
Nice guy, good lecturer.
